<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: </font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-21 04:39:56</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>There is another way to raise Qeynos faction, by killing the bandits in the Karanas.  Each kill will improve faction.  If you are able to enter the city, save the bandit sashes and turn them in to Paladin Chesgard at the paladin guild.  Each sash turned in will give you a small bit of experience and another improvement in faction.  I've heard that if the human form of Lord Grimrot is up and you don't kill him, that at 6pm game time he will despawn and the skeletal form of Lord Grimrot will spawn to replace him.  I haven't been able to verify this yet, because the one time I met the human form, I killed it.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
