<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Thelwin Boozehammer</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-23 21:56:24</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I was able to recieve my shield 2 days ago. Yay me! Still heres what you need to do for faction:<BR>
<BR>
Get 40 bandit sashes and go to the Temple of Thunder in S. Qeynos. Give the sashes to the guy next to the merchant with the shield, his nname as "Chesgurd" in it.  This is a great quest for faction as well as money. You will eventualy stop recieving faction of the PoL and so you dont need to give him anymore. You give lashun novashine about 500pp in 2gp sinctraments, and give him about 200 bone chips in the same fashion. Next go to qeynos and get about 16 rabid wolf pelts and about 4 rabid bear pelts. Go to the UFO and talk with a priestess and she will tell you about a "new disease". Turn these in and you should have enough faction. If you still do not have enough faction give lashun novashine about 200pp more in the same fashion of 2gp each time.<BR>
<BR>
Hopes this helps you all!<BR>
<BR>
 - 30th dwarven cleric of Bristlebane</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Prexus Cleric</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-30 02:08:50</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I just received the Shield as well. Instead of running around doing all the quest, I found an easier way to get Faction<BR>
You make an SK human and start it in Qeynos. You goto the pond below the cleric spinning orb and kill the little fish. Make sure to have your main character camped there as well.<BR>
Kill the fish and if there is a corpse, log your main character on. Loot the fish and turn the fish into the Roaming Paladin. You get a ton of faction and some xp. It take about 4 fish per faction level and the fish spawn every 6 minutes. Your new SK will be KOS after killing 4 fish. <BR>
This works really well if you have a partner that hills the fish and you loot.<BR>
You know you will have enough faction when you kill the putrid skellies or Grimrot and you get no faction adjustment for the Priests of Life.<BR>
I suggest once you get the faction to get the quest, you proceed to SK and kill the Putrid skellies to make Grimrot appear.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
