<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Nuts</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-03 03:58:09</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>1. it can NOT be recharged, notice it's *NO DROP* <BR>
2. it's going to be VERY VERY hard to camp it since either form is total resistance king!  You better not do it along, you will need a lvl 45+ enchanter or a lvl 49+ wizard, best to go with both class, make sure you drop it fast. the dot spell is deadly. otherwise, you will die very very stupidly.<BR>
3. DO NOT even try to kill Grimot when you are lower than lvl 45.  I have seen a lvl 50 cleric, died pitily over it.<BR>
4. you have to be *AIMABLY* to do the quest, and Aagis of Life, unfortunately, is a RANDOM reward.  that means, good luck.<BR>
<BR>
I have tried many times to get the quest from Mr. Picky Paladin, till I got a really good faction with him. and being all, i m a high elf cleric with 152 cha at the time (jewery gears). After I finally got the quest from him (at one point, he made me also wanting to kill him =P), I camped Grimot with 3 lvl 50 wizard friends for 2 weeks, believe me, i m not exaggrating, i almost died few times from his dot and fear spells. I hand in the 7th lore sycthe, and I got an Aegis of Life.  And I was wondering why the hell I do the quest for?  I have a paw of Opolla, a testament of Venear, and a charred guardian shield. Guess I am just a sick lvl 50 cleric bored out of his mind.<BR>
It's great to have the item, but it's really not worth the time and energy when you can obtain other substitutes easily.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
